UNBILLABLE RECEIVABLES ON

U.S. GOVERNMENT CONTRACTS ARISE WHEN THE SALES OR REVENUES BASED ON PERFORMANCE

ATTAINMENT, THOUGH APPROPRIATELY RECOGNIZED, CANNOT BE BILLED YET UNDER TERMS OF

THE CONTRACT. ACCOUNTS RECEIVABLE RELATED TO CLAIMS ARE ITEMS THAT THE COMPANY

BELIEVES ARE EARNED, BUT ARE SUBJECT TO UNCERTAINTY CONCERNING THEIR

DETERMINATION OR ULTIMATE REALIZATION.

